text.tspan:
Reported annual death rate from
maternal conditions
per 100,000 women and girls, based on official statistics
from each country. This includes late maternal deaths that occur up to 1 year after the end of pregnancy. Due to
limited reporting, figures are lower than the true number of maternal deaths.

Note: To allow for comparisons between countries and over time, this metric is
age-standardized
. All deaths in a country may not have been

registered with a
cause of death
.
